<subSubSection lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="42" pageNumber="321" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="42.[1381,2590,3336,3489]" lastBlockId="43.[795,1388,298,722]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="322" pageId="42" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Satunin" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[1386,1579,3407,3440]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Chionomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="42" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gud">Chionomys gud</taxonomicName>
is in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[1709,1787,3407,3440]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="42" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="roberti">roberti</taxonomicName>
species group. In the past, it was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martins" authorityYear="1842" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Chionomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="42" pageNumber="319" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nivalis">C. nivalis</taxonomicName>
. The two species differ in morphological details, karyotype, and molecular sequences. Phylogenetic reconstructions retrieved deeply divergent lineages of C. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Satunin" baseAuthorityYear="1909" box="[836,886,377,406]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Chionomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="43" pageNumber="322" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gud">gud</taxonomicName>
, with the population from Turkey (former subspecies lasistanius) recently ranked as a separate species. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
